<item>
            <title>[SPARK-15165] Codegen can break because toCommentSafeString is not actually safe</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-15165</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;toCommentSafeString method replaces &quot;\u&quot; with &quot;\ \u&quot; to avoid codegen breaking.&lt;br/&gt;
But if the even number of &quot;\&quot; is put before &quot;u&quot;, like &quot;\ \u&quot;, in the string literal in the query, codegen can break.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Following code causes compilation error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;val df = Seq(...).toDF
df.select(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;\\\\\\\\u002A/&apos;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).show
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason of the compilation error is because &quot;\\\\\\\\u002A/&quot; is translated into &quot;*/&quot; (the end of comment). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Due to this unsafety, arbitrary code can be injected like as follows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;val df = Seq(...).toDF
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Inject &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.exit(1)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;df.select(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;\\\\\\\\u002A/{&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.exit(1);}/*&apos;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).show
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
